stions-job-a4257526.html|title=The Londoner: Chris Mason lands Any Questions job|date=9 October 2019|website=London Evening Standard|url-status=live|access-date=9 October 2019}}</ref> He said it was \"daunting\" to take over from [[Jonathan Dimbleby]], who had been chair for 32 years. Mason suggested his Yorkshire accent helped him get the job and pointed at a lack of a broad range of regional accents more generally in British broadcasting.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/11/26/bbc-radio-4-host-chris-mason-yorkshire-accent-helped-get-questions/|title=BBC Radio 4 host Chris Mason: 'Yorkshire accent helped me get Any Questions? job' |date=26 November 2019|work=The Telegraph|accessdate=28 November 2019}}</ref> His first show was broadcast from the [[University of Reading]] on 18 October with guests [[Si\u00e2n Berry]], Madeline Grant, [[David Lammy]] and [[Brandon Lewis]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m0009d26|title=BBC Radio 4 \u2013 Any Questions?, Sian Berry, David Lammy MP, Brandon Lewis MP.|date=18 October 2019|publisher=BBC|url-status=live|access-date=18 October 2019}}</ref> \n\nIn October 2019, the website [[The Conservative Woman]] described Mason as \"mildly irreverent, self-deprecating and congenial... as well as being an experienced and highly competent political broadcaster\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.conservativewoman.co.uk/white-man-gets-bbc-job-what-went-wrong/|title=White man gets BBC job. What went wrong?|last=Oliver|first=Gary|date=11 October 2019|website=The Conservative Woman|url-status=live|access-date=18 October 2019}}</ref> \n\nMason is an occasional host of ''BBC Breakfast''.<ref name=\":0\" /> He is in discussions to join the forthcoming radio station and BBC Radio 4 competitor, [[Times Radio]] and confirmed he had been approached by them, saying it was a \"fascinating prospect for a station\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/feb/14/times-radio-offering-big-money-in-effort-to-lure-bbc-presenters-chris-mason-nick-robinson-news-uk|title=Times Radio offering big money in effort to lure BBC presenters|last=Waterson|first=Jim|date=15 February 2020|access-date=17 February 2020|work=The Guardian}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nMason has two children<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/stayingin/chris-mason-any-questions-radio-4-a4280891.html|title=Chris Mason: There\u2019s never been a better time in my lifetime to do this job|last=Luckhurst|first=Pheobe|date=7 November 2019|website=London Evening Standard|url-status=live|access-date=10 November 2019}}</ref> and lives in London. In July 2019, he took parental leave until September.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.responsesource.com/bulletin/news/bbc-news-correspondent-chris-mason-takes-leave/|title=BBC News correspondent Chris Mason takes leave|website=ResponseSource|url-status=live|access-date=7 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|id=4465475|name=Chris Mason}}\n* [https://twitter.com/ChrisMasonBBC?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Eauthor Chris Mason] on Twitter\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mason, Chris}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People educated at Ermysted's Grammar School]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Christ's College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Alumni of City, University of London]]\n[[Category:BBC newsreaders and journalists]]\n[[Category:British political journalists]]\n[[Category:British radio journalists]]\n[[Category:British television journalists]]\n[[Category:21st-century British journalists]]\n[[Category:People from Yorkshire]]\n[[Category:ITN newsreaders and journalists]]\n[[Category:English radio presenters]]\n[[Category:English television presenters]]\n", "name_user": "Martinevans123", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePersonal life:adjust +link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chris_Mason_(journalist)"}
