v5      = ''[[Revolver (magazine)|Revolver]]''\n| rev5score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite journal |last=Ciavarella |first=Liz |date=August 2009 |title=Carving out the Eyes of God review |journal=Revolver |publisher=Future |issue=83 |page=74 |issn=1527-408X}}</ref>\n| rev6      = Thrash Hits\n| rev6Score = {{Rating|5|6}}<ref name=\"Thrash Hits\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thrashhits.com/2009/07/album-goatwhore-carving-out-the-eyes-of-god/|title=Album: Goatwhore - Carving out the Eyes of God|author= |publisher=Thrash Hits|date=July 2, 2009|accessdate=January 27, 2012}}</ref>\n| noprose   = yes\n}}<!-- Automatically generated by DASHBot-->\n\n'''''Carving Out the Eyes of God''''' is the fourth studio album by American [[Blackened death metal|death metal]] band [[Goatwhore]]. The first single of the album, \"Apocalyptic Havoc\", was featured in three games: ''[[Splatterhouse (2010 video game)|Splatterhouse]]'', ''[[Saints Row: The Third]]'' and ''[[Tap Tap Revenge 3]]''.\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n|title1   = Apocalyptic Havoc\n|length1  = 3:16\n|title2   = The All-Destroying\n|length2  = 3:14\n|title3   = Carving Out the Eyes of God\n|length3  = 4:20\n|title4   = Shadow of a Rising Knife\n|length4  = 4:39\n|title5   = Provoking the Ritual of Death\n|length5  = 3:43\n|title6   = In Legions, I Am Wars of Wrath\n|length6  = 4:34\n|title7   = Reckoning of the Soul Made Godless\n|length7  = 3:51\n|title8   = This Passing into the Power of Demons\n|length8  = 4:27\n|title9   = Razor Flesh Devoured\n|length9  = 4:18\n|title10  = To Mourn and Forever Wander Through Forgotten Doorways\n|length10 = 4:19\n}}\n\n== Personnel ==\n* Ben Falgoust \u2013 [[Lead vocalist|lead vocals]]\n* Sammy Duet \u2013 [[Electric guitar|guitar]]s, [[Backing vocalist|backing vocals]]\n* Nathan Bergeron \u2013 [[Bass guitar|bass]], backing vocals\n* Zack Simmons \u2013 [[Drum kit|drums]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Goatwhore}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Carving out the Eyes of God}}\n\n[[Ca