lish band)|Rainbow]] - ''[[Straight Between the Eyes]]''\n* Rapid Tears - ''Honestly''\n* [[Raven (British band)|Raven]] - ''Crash Bang Wallop'' (EP)\n* Raven - ''[[Wiped Out (Raven album)|Wiped Out]]''\n* [[Resurrection Band]] - ''[[D.M.Z. (Resurrection Band album)|D.M.Z.]]''\n* Riff Raff - ''Robot Stud''\n* [[Riot (band)|Riot]] - ''[[Restless Breed]]''\n* Riot - ''[[Riot Live (EP)|Riot Live]]'' (EP)\n* [[The Rods]] - ''Wild Dogs''\n* [[Rose Tattoo]] - ''[[Scarred for Life (Rose Tattoo album)|Scarred for Life]]''\n* [[Rush (band)|Rush]] - ''[[Signals (Rush album)|Signals]]''\n* [[Samson (band)|Samson]] - ''Losing My Grip'' (EP) \n* Samson  -  ''[[Before the Storm (Samson album)|Before the Storm]]''\n* Santers - ''Mayday'' (EP)\n* Santers - ''Racing Time''\n* [[Saxon (band)|Saxon]] - ''[[The Eagle Has Landed (album)|The Eagle Has Landed]]'' (live)\n* [[Scorpions (band)|Scorpions]] - ''[[Blackout (Scorpions album)|Blackout]]''\n* [[Shark Island (band)|Sharks]] - ''Altar Ego''\n* Shiva - ''Firedance''\n* [[Sinner (band)|Sinner]] - ''Wild 'n' Evil''\n* Speed Queen - ''Speed Queen'', aka ''II''\n* Split Beaver - ''When Hell Won't Have You''\n* Squadron - ''First Mission''\n* [[Stampede (band)|Stampede]] - ''Days of Wine and Roses'' (EP)\n* Stampede - ''The Official Bootleg'' (live)\n* Street Fighter - ''Feel the Noise''\n* [[Stress (Brazil band)|Stress]] - ''[[Stress (Stress album)|Stress]]''\n* [[Billy Sheehan#Talas|Talas]] - ''Sink Your Teeth Into That''\n* [[Tank (band)|Tank]] - ''[[Filth Hounds of Hades]]''\n* Tank - ''[[Power of the Hunter]]''\n* Teeze (CA) - ''Teeze'' (EP)\n* [[38 Special (band)|38 Special]] - ''[[Special Forces (38 Special album)|Special Forces]]''\n* [[TNT (Norwegian band)|TNT]] - ''[[TNT (TNT album)|TNT]]''\n* Torch - ''Fire Raiser'' (EP)\n* [[Bernie Torm\u00e9]]  \u2013 ''Turn Out the Lights''\n* [[Trance (band)|Trance]] - ''Break Out''\n* [[Trust (French band)|Trust]] - ''Savage''\n* [[Twisted Sister]] - ''Ruff Cuts'' (EP)\n* Twisted Sister - ''[[Under the Blade]]''\n* [[Tygers of Pan Tang]] - ''[[The Cage (Tygers of Pan Tang album)|The Cage]]''\n* [[Tytan (band)|Tytan]] - ''Blind Men and Fools'' (EP)\n* [[UFO (band)|UFO]] - ''[[Mechanix (album)|Mechanix]]''\n* [[Uriah Heep (band)|Uriah Heep]] - ''[[Abominog]]''\n* [[Vanadium (band)|Vanadium]] - ''Metal Rock''\n* [[Vandenberg (band)|Vandenberg]] - ''[[Vandenberg (album)|Vandenberg]]''\n* [[Van Halen]] - ''[[Diver Down]]''\n* [[Vardis]] - ''Quo Vardis''\n* Vendetta (US) - ''Vendetta''\n* [[Venom (band)|Venom]] - ''[[Black Metal (album)|Black Metal]]''\n* [[Virgin Steele]] - ''[[Virgin Steele (album)|Virgin Steele]]''\n* Viva \u2013 ''Dealers of the Night''\n* Voie De Fait - ''Ange ou D\u00e9mon''\n* [[Warning (French band)|Warning]] - ''Warning II''\n* [[Whitesnake]] - ''[[Saints & Sinners (Whitesnake album)|Saints & Sinners]]''\n* [[Witchfinder General (band)|Witchfinder General]]  \u2013 ''[[Soviet Invasion (album)|Soviet Invasion]] (EP)\n* [[Witchfinder General (band)|Witchfinder General]] - ''[[Death Penalty (album)|Death Penalty]]''\n* [[Y&T]] - ''[[Black Tiger (album)|Black Tiger]]''\n* Zero Nine \u2013 ''Blank Verse''\n* Zero Nine \u2013 ''Visions, Scenes and Dreams''\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Events==\n* Iron Maiden's first album with Bruce Dickinson, ''[[The Number of the Beast (album)|The Number of the Beast]]'', reaches No.1 in the U.K. music charts.\n* [[Mot\u00f6rhead]]'s guitarist [[Eddie Clarke (musician)|\"Fast\" Eddie Clarke]] leaves the band and is replaced by ex-[[Thin Lizzy]] guitarist [[Brian Robertson (guitarist)|Brian Robertson]].\n* [[Judas Priest]]'s single \"[[You've Got Another Thing Comin']]\" is released. It will go on to become the band's best selling single.\n* [[Ozzy Osbourne]]'s guitarist [[Randy Rhoads]] dies in an airplane accident on March 19.\n* [[Iron Maiden]]'s drummer [[Clive Burr]] is fired from the band because of personal and tour-schedule problems. [[Nicko McBrain]] from [[Trust (French band)|Trust]] is hired to replace him.\n* [[Ace Frehley]], Space Ace and lead guitarist of [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]], leaves the band. [[Vinnie Vincent]] takes his place. \n* [[Queen (band)|Queen]] departs from their hard rock legacy with the ill-received funk/disco album ''[[Hot Space]]''.\n* December: Former [[Deep Purple]] vocalist [[Ian Gillan]] replaces [[Ronnie James Dio]] in [[Black Sabbath]].\n* The band [[Metallica]] leaves Los Angeles and relocates to the [[San Francisco Bay Area]].\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Timeline box|title=[[Timeline of heavy metal music|Heavy Metal Timeline]]|before=[[1981 in heavy metal music|1981]]|after=[[1983 in heavy metal music|1983]]|year='''1982'''}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Timeline of heavy metal and hard rock music}}\n\n[[Category:1980s in heavy metal music]]\n[[Category:1982 in music|Metal]]\n", "text_old": "{{Year in music|1982}}\n{{Year nav topic5|1982|heavy metal music}}\n\n{{unreferenced|date=February 2015}}This is a timeline documenting the events of [[Heavy Metal music|heavy metal]] in the year 1982.\n\n==Newly formed bands==\n\n*[[Abattoir (band)|Abattoir]] \n*[[Armored Saint]]\n* [[Artillery (band)|Artillery]]\n*[[Brocas Helm (band)|Brocas Helm]] \n* [[Corrosion of Conformity]] (not originally a metal band)\n*[[Crumbsuckers]]\n* [[Death Angel]]\n* [[Destruction (band)|Destruction]]\n* [[Dio (band)|Dio]]\n* [[Dirty Rotten Imbeciles]]\n*[[Fates Warning]]\n* [[Godflesh]] (under the name \"Fall of Because\" until 1988)\n*[[Guardian (band)|Guardian]] \n*[[Hell (British band)|Hell]] \n*[[Hellhammer]]\n*[[Hellion (band)|Hellion]] \n*[[Kreator]]\n*[[L\u0227\u0227z Rockit]]\n*[[Luzbel]]\n*[[No Mercy (metal band)|No Mercy]] \n*[[Obsession (band)|Obsession]] \n*[[Onslaught (band)|Onslaught]] \n*[[Tankard (band)|Tankard]] \n*[[Terra Rosa (band)|Terra Rosa]] \n*[[TNT (Norwegian band)|TNT]] \n*[[Tredegar (band)|Tredegar]] \n* [[Steve Vai]]\n*[[Voivod (band)|Voivod]]\n*[[W.A.S.P. (band)|W.A.S.P.]]\n*[[Warriors (band)|Warriors]]\n*[[Watchtower (band)|Watchtower]]\n*[[X Japan|X]] (later known as X Japan)\n*[[Znowhite]]\n\n==Albums & EPs==\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[Lee Aaron]] - ''[[The Lee Aaron Project]]''\n* [[Accept (band)|Accept]] - ''[[Restless and Wild]]''\n* Acid - ''Acid''\n* [[Aerosmith]] - ''[[Rock in a Hard Place]]''\n* [[Alice Cooper]] - ''[[Zipper Catches Skin]]''\n* Americade - ''American Metal''\n* [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]] - ''[[Metal on Metal]]''\n* [[April Wine]] - ''[[Power Play (April Wine album)|Power Play]]''\n* August Redmoon - ''Fools Are Never Alone'' (EP)\n* [[Axewitch]] - ''[[Pray for Metal]]'' (EP)\n* [[Steve Riley (drummer)|The B'zz]] \u2013 ''Get Up''\n* [[Bar\u00f3n Rojo]] - ''[[Volumen brutal]]''\n* Beast (Ger) - ''Beast''\n* Bengal Tigers - ''Metal Fetish'' (EP)\n* [[Bitch (band)|Bitch]] - ''[[Damnation Alley (album)|Damnation Alley]]'' (EP)\n* Bitches Sin - ''Predator''\n* [[Blackfoot (band)|Blackfoot]] - ''Highway Song Live!'' \n* [[Black Sabbath]] - ''[[Live Evil (Black Sabbath album)|Live Evil]]'' \n* [[Blue \u00d6yster Cult]] - ''[[Extraterrestrial Live]]'' \n* [[Bodine (band)|Bodine]] - ''Bold as Brass''\n* [[Bow Wow (band)|Bow Wow]] \u2013 ''Asian Volcano''\n* [[Bow Wow (band)|Bow Wow]] \u2013 ''Warning From Stardust''\n* [[Budgie (band)|Budgie]] - ''[[Deliver Us from Evil (Budgie album)|Deliver Us from Evil]]''\n* Breaker (Can) - ''In Days of Heavy Metal'' (EP)\n* Breslau - ''Volksmusik''\n* [[Cheap Trick]] - ''[[One on One (Cheap Trick album)|One on One]]''\n* Cintron - ''Cintron'' (EP)\n* [[Cloven Hoof (band)|Cloven Hoof]] - ''[[The Opening Ritual]]'' (EP)\n* [[Coney Hatch]] - ''[[Coney Hatch (album)|Coney Hatch]]''\n* [[Alice Cooper]] - ''[[Zipper Catches Skin]]''\n* [[Demon (band)|Demon]] - ''The Unexpected Guest'' \n* Demon Flight - ''Demon Flight'' (EP)\n* [[Diamond Head (English band)|Diamond Head]]  -  ''[[Borrowed Time (Diamond Head album)|Borrowed Time]]''\n* Dietrich - ''Dietrich'' (EP)\n* [[E.F. Band]] - ''Deep Cut''\n* Fargo - ''F''\n* [[Fist (UK band)|Fist (UK)]] - ''Back with a Vengean